@page "/privacy"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<div class="legal-container">
    <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>What data does RSS Reader collect?</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>An anonymized account identifier</strong> &mdash; your Microsoft email address is never stored. We use an opaque identifier provided by Microsoft to link your account.</li>
            <li><strong>Feeds you subscribe to</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Feed item metadata</strong> &mdash; text content, tags, read/unread status, saved posts</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            You are trusting <strong>me</strong> (Brandon) and the <strong>RSS Reader code &amp; infrastructure</strong> with the above data.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>How is that data used?</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>This data is used solely for authentication and app functionality.</li>
            <li>No third-party analytics or ad services are provisioned in the infrastructure.</li>
            <li>No data is shared with third parties except Microsoft/Azure as the cloud provider.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Email anonymization</h2>
        <p>
            When you sign in with your Microsoft account, RSS Reader receives an opaque account identifier from Azure Active Directory.
            <strong>Your email address is never written to our database.</strong>
            We cannot see, search, or recover your email from the identifier we store.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Microsoft account required</h2>
        <p>
            A personal Microsoft account is required to log in. Microsoft securely handles the authentication &mdash; your credentials are never exposed to RSS Reader.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Alternative options</h2>
        <p>If you prefer not to use a Microsoft account at all:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Self-host the app</strong> for absolute privacy &mdash; <a href="https://github.com/brandonchastain/rss-reader/blob/main/README.md">Docs</a></li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>Security</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All data is stored on an encrypted Azure Storage Account.</li>
            <li>The backend server runs in an Azure Container App (Azure-managed PaaS).</li>
            <li>Error logs are sent to Azure Log Analytics and retained for 30 days.</li>
            <li>All network traffic is protected by HTTPS.</li>
            <li>The backend has two layers of authentication: a verified Microsoft identity <em>and</em> a frontend-origin secret key.</li>
            <li>The API prevents users from accessing any data that isn&rsquo;t their own.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>No spam</h2>
        <p>We don&rsquo;t send any emails at all. We don&rsquo;t even have your email address.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>We will never share or sell any personal data.</h2>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section legal-gdpr">
        <h2>GDPR Notice</h2>
        <p>If you are an EU resident, the following applies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Data is processed solely to provide app functionality and authentication, based on your consent when you use RSS Reader.</li>
            <li><strong>Your Rights:</strong> You have the right to access, correct, delete, restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data. You may also request a copy of your data.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Retention:</strong> Your data is retained only as long as your account exists. When the account deletion feature is available, you will be able to remove your data at any time.</li>
            <li><strong>International Transfers:</strong> Data is stored in Microsoft Azure data centers in the United States.</li>
            <li><strong>Contact:</strong> To exercise your rights or for privacy concerns, please open an issue in <a href="https://github.com/brandonchastain/rss-reader">this repository</a>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>RSS Reader is primarily intended for US users, but basic GDPR protections are provided for EU residents.</p>
    </section>
</div>
